@demographics
go-to: menu

**Demographic Groups**

**Working Class**: Blue-collar workers in factories, workshops, mines, transport, and relief jobs. Most support either the Democratic Party or the SPA. They make up 40-50% of the population.

**Old Middle Class**: Independent shopkeepers, small business owners, professionals, and local proprietors. They tend to be conservative and are one of the strongest bases for the far right. 10-15% of the population.

**New Middle Class**: White-collar workers, clerks, teachers, and public employees. This is a major base for liberal and reform politics. 10-15% of the population.

**Rural**: Small farmers, tenant farmers, large farmers, and independent rural workers. Their politics split between Democratic relief politics, Farmer-Labor insurgency, the GOP, and agrarian right-populism. 20-30% of the population.

**Catholics** are the largest religious minority, at about 30% of the population. They are politically mixed, with strong urban Democratic machines, labor networks, and some anti-New Deal conservative constituencies.

**Jews** account for between 0.5% to 1% of the population, and tend to support liberal, Democratic, and socialist currents while facing escalating pressure from the far right.


